      "message": "[Minor] Line 306: The method documentation is now stale: it still says the WakeLock and synchronous account reactivation run unconditionally, but the new normal-priority background path skips both. This can mislead future changes around push handling. Update the comment to describe the new behavior explicitly.\n\n```suggestion\n     *  For normal-priority pushes received while the app is already in background,\n     *  skip starting the foreground service, WakeLock acquisition, and synchronous\n     *  account reactivation to avoid unnecessary battery / Doze impact. High-priority\n     *  pushes still perform full processing so the daemon can complete decryption.\n```",
